Low engine oil level warning indicator. Values: 0 = normal, 1 = low oil warning.
Battery not charging warning indicator. Values: 0 = off, 1 = on. Indicates that the low-voltage system battery is not being charged (alternator/DC-DC issue).

0 - No key in lock 1 - Key in lock
0 - Not present 1 - Present
Computation Approach: (CAN Front Passenger Presence), avl_io_945 (CSF Front Passenger Present)

Description: Airbag system state from CAN bus. Values: 0 = airbag system inactive/normal, 1 = airbag system active/warning. Indicates airbag system status and potential safety issues.

Electric Power Steering (EPS) system state. Values: 0 = inactive/normal, 1 = active/warning. Indicates EPS system operational status. When active, the EPS system is engaged and assisting steering. Warning state may indicate system faults or reduced assistance. Read from CAN bus.

Trailer axle lift active status. Array of boolean values, one per trailer axle. Values: false = axle down (normal position), true = axle lifted. Used for load distribution control and to reduce wear on specific axles when trailer is empty or lightly loaded. Read from CAN bus.
Computation Approach: (CAN Trailer Axle Lift Active 1), can_trailer_axle_lift_active_2 (CAN Trailer Axle Lift Active 2)

Digital input 1 state. Values: 0 = low/inactive, 1 = high/active. Semantic meaning (e.g., ignition, door sensor) is defined in `asset.installation.*` metadata. Used to compute canonical fields like `power.ignition`. If only bitmask is available, transformation pipeline extracts bit 0.
Digital input 2 state. Values: 0 = low/inactive, 1 = high/active. Semantic meaning defined in installation metadata. If only bitmask is available, transformation pipeline extracts bit 1.
Digital input 3 state. Values: 0 = low/inactive, 1 = high/active. Semantic meaning defined in installation metadata. If only bitmask is available, transformation pipeline extracts bit 2.

Digital input 4 state (also functions as pulse counter). Values: 0 = low/inactive, 1 = high/active. Pulse count resets when records are saved. Semantic meaning defined in installation metadata. If only bitmask is available, transformation pipeline extracts bit 3.
Computation Approach: (Pulse Counter Din1), din (Digital Inputs Bitmask, bit 3)

Description: Digital output 1 state. Values: 0 = inactive, 1 = active. Semantic meaning (e.g., immobilizer relay) is defined in `asset.installation.*` metadata. Used for immobilization control and status computation. If only bitmask is available, transformation pipeline extracts bit 0.
Digital output 2 state. Values: 0 = inactive, 1 = active. Semantic meaning defined in installation metadata. If only bitmask is available, transformation pipeline extracts bit 1.
Digital output 3 state. Values: 0 = inactive, 1 = active. Semantic meaning defined in installation metadata. If only bitmask is available, transformation pipeline extracts bit 2.
